{
  "texts": [
    "'Do' (LogDice: 8.29997) is another strong collocate, often used to attribute actions or tasks to ChatGPT.",
    "This grammatical structure reinforces ChatGPT's role as an active entity capable of carrying out tasks or functions.",
    "Many of these instances are examples of personalisation ('ChatGPT did great, though', 'I'm really curious what ChatGPT does with the code you ask it to explain').",
    "Equally, there are many negated constructions that state how much ChatGPT does not know ('ChatGPT does not seem to have memory', 'Chat-GPT does n ot know either what's in the demo today').",
    "In other instances, users express what ChatGPT is capable of ('ChatGPT does surprisingly well on a Named Entity Recognition task')."
  ]
}